    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn diff mode, <kbd>PageUp</kbd> does not scroll upward if the cursor is located below many deleted lines (almost twice as long as the terminal height?).\r\nThis bisects to 88d13d2778a4fab3fdcc2bf4c1adf631b38ea3ce (#23320).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSet the terminal size to 80Ã—24.\r\nPrepare the files:\r\n```shell\r\n> a python3 -c 'print(\"\\n\".join([\"^^^\"] * 2 + [\"$$$\"] * 2))'\r\n> b python3 -c 'print(\"\\n\".join([\"^^^\"] * 2 + [\"###\"] * 42 + [\"$$$\"] * 2))'\r\n```\r\n\r\n(The issue happens when `b` has 41 or more `###` lines)\r\nOpen the files in diff mode:\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -d --clean a b\r\n```\r\n\r\nGo to the bottom (<kbd>G</kbd>) and then try to scroll up (<kbd>PageUp</kbd>)&mdash;the cursor does not move from the 3rd line. <kbd>k</kbd> works as expected.\r\n\r\n![PageUp](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/11627708/bceb62ba-f3a9-430e-addc-49cc63d35f08)\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n<kbd>PageUp</kbd> scrolls upward and the cursor goes to the 2nd line.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-1264+geb1f0e8fcca7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.0.1969\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.48.2 using VTE 0.74.0 +BIDI +GNUTLS +ICU +SYSTEMD\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256cololr\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
